text:
The following are qualities that make the Masters unique:
* The smallest field of all four golf tournaments;
* The only tournament in which a driver may advance to the next round;
* The only tournament in which the winner is determined by a tiebreaker (best 2 teams), rather than a best-of-seven playoff;
* The only winner-take-all playoff (best 2 teams win both rounds and a tiebreaker is played if a single team wins both rounds);
* The competition's top player may not participate due to injury;
